Either it will install the packages based on the commit hash stated in your `composer.lock`, if it exists on the repository, just ignoring the mismatch between the commit and the version, either it will fail with a pretty straight forwardly expressed reason: ***&quot;history was rewritten?&quot;***

----

The question did pique my curiosity: I would have said yes, because otherwise, locking the commit hash in the lock file would be useless, but I had to test it for the sake of correctness.

